{{Infobox language |name=Riang |nativename= |states=[[Burma]], [[China]] |ethnicity=[[Palaung people|Palaung]] |speakers={{sigfig|27,500|2}} |date=1995–2008 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Palaungic languages|Palaungic]] |fam3=Palaung–Riang |fam4= |nation= |lc1=ril|ld1=Riang Lang |lc2=yin|ld2=Yinchia |glotto=rian1260 |glottorefname=Riang }}
'''Riang''' is a Mon–Khmer language of Burma and China. Speakers are culturally assimilated with the [[Karen people|Karen]], but are [[Palaung people|Palaung]] by ancestry and their language is unrelated. Riang Lang and Riang Lai (Yinchia) are sometimes considered distinct languages.
