'''Úrsula Heinze de Lorenzo''' (born in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]] on 18 June 1941]) is a writer and translator in Galician and German residing in [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]]. Her extensive literary works include poetry, novels, essays, short stories and children's literature. She moved from Germany to Galicia in 1968.<ref>http://www.xerais.es/cgigeneral/ficha_autor.pl?id_autor=112811&id_sello_editorial_web=13&id_funcion=44</ref> She has worked for the Radio Galega [[Compañía de Radio Televisión de Galicia]] and El Correo Gallego and is a former President of the [[International PEN|PEN]] club of Galicia.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=thba9JxuDXAC&pg=PA257&dq=ursula+heinze&hl=en&ei=KmOpTIrlAcGB8gaK75D9DA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=ursula%20heinze&f=false The Feminist Encyclopedia of Spanish Literature: A-M by Janet Pérez and Maureen Ihrie, pg 257]</ref>
